review_blob: On tap at brewery. Yellow with fruity and grassy aroma. Chewy palate. Fine carbonation. Nice sweet and sour balance to make this one of the easiest sours Ive ever tried.
On tap at brewery. Smells like an indian restaurant. Black as night, little to no head. Great mouth feel with curry tingling on the edges of the tongue. Great kick at the end.
From bottle. Zero head. Yellow color typical of tripels. Sweet aroma. Fine carbonation gives it a great mouth feel. Sweet but ends with a grassy bitterness.

Had an emotional experience with this beer. Lots of citrus hops and great mouth feel. Full head and not as much jasmine as expected. Can feel the bitterness in the outside of the mouth and middle of the tongue.
On tap. Pine aroma. Citrusy, bitter hops with a sweeter finish. A bit sticky in the back of the throat.
On tap. Poured yellow with medium head. Aroma grassy and floral. Chewy rose, sweet but complex enough to score big.
Bomber. Cola colored pour. Not enough smoke to match the vanilla flavor. A little syrupy.
Bomber. Apple aroma and more apple notes. Mild for a farmhouse but complex and easy to drink.
Bomber. Pours yellow with grassy aroma. Very fine carbonanation. Sweet with apple notes. Very crisp with little aftertaste.
On tap. Cloudy with big cherry aroma. Consistency a little syrupy. Big cherry notes with an alcohol finish.
On tap. Big wine flavor that sits on everything else. Fine carbonation with very little head.
On tap. Great aroma and golden hue appearance. Sweet and grassy. Classic tripel flavor.
On tap. Not very interesting or complex. Flat finish that reminds me of a light beer.
On tap, a favorite of mine. Great golden color and sweet aroma. Smooth for an 8.5. Bready with a little caramel and apple. Great mouth feel with a little bitterness at the finish.
beer_name: Boulevard Smokestack Series - Tank 7 Farmhouse Ale

review_blob: On tap. Big citrus aroma. Red appearance. Big citrus hops and bitter aftertaste. Good, balanced and interesting IPA.
On tap. Brown sugar and cinnamon toast aroma. Opaque pour with thick, beige head. Warm mouth feel and subtle flavor with a big flavor kick at the finish: licorice and toffee.
On tap. Sweet cherry aroma. Cola pour. Sweet toffee, chocolate, cherry notes with a tosty finish. Moves great through the mouth. Sweet, but good.
Tap at Churchkey. Subtle but sweet aroma. Light and cloudy appearance. Grassy hops with a stronger grass finish.
On draft. Pale yellow color with tiny bubbles. Grassy saison with a strong basil finish. Great mouth feel with developing flavor that gets more grassy as it warms.
